-- TABLE-Brazil's IGP-M price index falls 0.13 pct in March
-- 
-- Thu May 29, 2014 08:12AM EDT
-- None



RIO DE JANEIRO, March 29 (Reuters) - Brazil's broadest price index, the IGP-M <BRIGP=ECI>, fell 0.13 percent in May compared with a 0.78 percent rise in April, the Getulio Vargas Foundation, a Brazilian economic research and teaching institute, said on Thursday.

The index had been expected to fall 0.01 percent, according to the median forecast of 25 economists polled by Reuters. <BRIGP=ECI> In the 12 months through June, the IGP-M index rose 7.84 percent, up from 7.98 percent in the previous month.